### Angular version
 
The supported Angular version is <font color=red>`^18.0.0`</font>.
 

### 1. Create a project

It is recommended to use `@angular/cli` to create your project.

```bash
ng new New-Project
```

### 2. Installation

Go to your project folder and use npm to install DevUI.

```bash
npm i ng-devui
# Optional. Font icon library
# npm i @devui-design/icons
```

### 3. Import Modules

```typescript
import { BrowserModule } from '@angular/platform-browser';
// Some DevUI components depend on the Angular animation, and the animations module needs to be introduced.
import { BrowserAnimationsModule } from' @angular/platform-browser/animations';
import { NgModule } from '@angular/core';
import { DevUIModule } from 'ng-devui';
import { AppComponent } from './app.component';

@NgModule({
  declarations: [
    AppComponent
  ],
  imports: [
    BrowserModule,
    BrowserAnimationsModule,
    DevUIModule
  ],
  bootstrap: [ AppComponent ],
  })
export class AppModule {}

```

### 4. Import Styles

Add the devui style to the `angular.json` file.

```json
{
  "styles": [
    ...
    "node_modules/ng-devui/devui.min.css"
  ]
}
```

### 5. Start Development and Debugging

```bash
ng serve --open
```
